Interface AppointmentService

All Known Implementing Classes:
AppointmentServiceImpl
public interface AppointmentService
This interface defines the operations available for managing appointments, appointment slots, and appointment outcomes within the system.

    • scheduleAppointment

      void scheduleAppointment(String patientID, String doctorID, String dateOfChoice, String startTime, String endTime)
      Schedules an appointment for a patient with a specific doctor.
      Parameters:
      patientID - the unique identifier of the patient
      doctorID - the unique identifier of the doctor
      dateOfChoice - the desired date for the appointment in string format
      startTime - the start time of the appointment
      endTime - the end time of the appointment

      boolean addAppointmentSlot(String doctorID, String startTime, String endTime, Date date)
      Adds a new appointment slot for a doctor.
      Parameters:
      doctorID - the unique identifier of the doctor
      startTime - the start time of the appointment slot
      endTime - the end time of the appointment slot
      date - the date for which the appointment slot is being added
      Returns:
      true if the slot is successfully added, false otherwise

    • addAppointmentOutcome

      void addAppointmentOutcome(String appointmentOutcomeID, Appointment appointment, MedicalRecord medicalRecord, String consultationNotes, PrescriptionStatus status)
      Adds the outcome of a specific appointment.
      Parameters:
      appointmentOutcomeID - the unique identifier of the appointment outcome
      appointment - the appointment related to the outcome
      medicalRecord - the medical record associated with the appointment
      consultationNotes - the notes from the consultation
      status - the status of the prescription related to the appointment
